post_text: The district will operate on a two hour delay on Monday, February 25, 2019. Please note that some buses may be delayed because of rerouting due to road closures. Additionally, there are pockets of our communities that are still without electricity. If your child is unable to attend school today because of weather related issues, please send in a note to the principal upon their return. This will be an excused absence.

post_text:
Two Hour Early Dismissal on Wednesday, September 5, 2018

September 4, 2018

Dear Parents and Guardians:

Due to the continued high heat and humidity, Kiski Area School District is operating on a Two-Hour Early Dismissal on Wednesday, September 5, 2018. Students in all schools will be dismissed two hours earlier than the regularly scheduled time.

As a reminder, the Meet the Teacher and Open House events scheduled for Wednesday, September 5, and Thursday, September 6, are postponed until further notice. Students will report to school at regularly scheduled times on those days.

Thank you for your continued cooperation.

Sincerely,

Dr. Timothy P. Scott
Superintendent

post_text:
Commencement will be Inside on June 1, 2018 at 6:30 p.m.

This is to inform you that the graduation ceremonies will be held in the Kiski Area High School Gymnasium this evening due to weather concerns. The ceremony will begin at 6:30pm. Each graduate received 4 tickets for the event this morning. This ensures that all students have their close family members in the gymnasium during the ceremony. Please know that all other attendees will be able to view a live stream of the event in the auditorium and LGI without a ticket. These areas are air conditioned and provide a comfortable viewing location. Thank you and we will see you this evening to honor the class of 2018.
